commitResults.messageTitle: Add OS time display to Person
commitResults.messageBody:
PersonCard does not display local time zones which is required
by the user to ensure he contacts clients at appropriate times.

Let's add in a Time class which is also included in a Person,
this way we can access the local time of the person to be displayed
through PersonCard.

Test cases have been added to ensure time displayed is accurate and
correct.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add country and company attributes to Person
commitResults.messageBody:
The add command currently uses 'address' as an attribute of Person.
This attribute name does not fit the intended usage.

Let's rename the 'address' attribute to 'country' throughout the
codebase. In addition, let's introduce a new 'company' attribute
that shares the same input constraints as 'country'.

Test cases have also been updated and added to ensure the
correctness of the modified and newly introduced attributes.

These changes support the direction of the model for our
target audience.

Some sentences had trailing
whitespaces as well as no newline
at the end of the file.

Let's add newlines and remove
trailing whitespaces to adhere
to checkstyle.

commitResults.messageTitle: Handle brackets, duplicates, and special chars
commitResults.messageBody:
Remove square brackets around patterns like "[ command/]" in user inputs
and ensure they are not treated as commands. The app now considers a
duplicate only if another contact has the same phone or email, and
displays a warning before adding such contacts. Users can proceed by
entering 'y' or cancel with 'n'. Also added support for special
characters in contact names and the local part of emails.

* Test constructors, execute(), equals(), and toString()
* Refactor ModelStubs into a single reusable file
* Add package-private constructor for testing null pendingPerson

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix confirmation bug and remove CancelAddCommand
commitResults.messageBody:
Fixed a bug where typing another command during a confirmation prompt
caused unexpected behavior. Now, any input other than 'y' will cancel
the confirmation safely.

Deleted CancelAddCommand and its corresponding test, as confirmation
cancellation is now handled in a unified way across all commands.

commitResults.messageTitle: fix(contact): lowercase emails to avoid duplicates
commitResults.messageBody:
User emails are now automatically converted to lowercase before saving a
new contact. This ensures consistent handling of email addresses and
prevents duplicate entries caused by case differences.

commitResults.messageTitle: feat: add confirmation flow for duplicate commands
commitResults.messageBody:
Introduced a confirmation mechanism for commands that may require user
approval (e.g. adding a duplicate contact).

* Added ConfirmableCommand interface to mark commands that support
  confirmation before execution.
* Updated AddCommand to implement ConfirmableCommand and handle
  duplicate contact confirmation logic.
* Extended CommandResult with an optional confirmMessage field to
  signal when user confirmation is needed.
* Modified AddressBookParser to recognize confirm commands ('y')
  and route them correctly.
* Moved confirmation state handling to LogicManager to centralize
  pending command tracking and ensure consistent execution flow.

This change fixes a bug where 'y' could unintentionally re-execute
non-confirmable commands and prepares the codebase for future
commands that require confirmation.

commitResults.messageTitle: Remove low-use confirm classes, update tests
commitResults.messageBody:
Removed ConfirmAddCommand and ConfirmableCommand as they were rarely
used. Refactored AddressBookParser and related logic to maintain
clean flow and behavior without these classes.

Added and updated test cases to cover pending command execution
and ensure full code coverage in the parser, preserving correct
handling of 'y' input and clearing of pending commands.

commitResults.messageBody:

commitResults.messageTitle: test: Add JUnit tests for edge cases and error handling
commitResults.messageBody:
* ArgumentTokenizer handles square brackets in prefixes correctly
* AddressBookParser tests confirmation flow and pending commands
* Email enforces lowercase storage and case-insensitive equality
* TimezoneMapper trims whitespace and handles mixed-case country names
* PersonList allows adding persons with duplicate phone numbers
* EditCommand detects no-change edits and throws appropriate exception
* TimeFormatter verifies formatting at midnight boundary

Improves coverage and prevents regressions in edge cases, flows,
case sensitivity, and parser logic.

Add three Java assert statements to the AddCommand class for better
debugging and validation:
* In the constructor, after requireNonNull(person), to reinforce the
  non-null invariant.
* In execute, after requireNonNull(model), to assert pre-conditions
  for model and toAdd.
* In execute, after model.addPerson(toAdd), to assert the
  post-condition that the person was added.

Add test to test null model handling,
covering pre-condition asserts.
